Try the code like this?
```java
    @Autowired
    private ISessionPool sessionPool;

    @Test
    public void test_insertTablet() {
        List<MeasurementSchema> schemas = new ArrayList<>();
        schemas.add(new MeasurementSchema("x", TSDataType.DOUBLE, TSEncoding.RLE, CompressionType.SNAPPY));
        schemas.add(new MeasurementSchema("y", TSDataType.DOUBLE, TSEncoding.RLE, CompressionType.SNAPPY));
        schemas.add(new MeasurementSchema("speed", TSDataType.DOUBLE, TSEncoding.GORILLA, CompressionType.SNAPPY));

        String deviceId = "root.rt.tablet.d01";
        int size = 1000;
        Tablet tablet = new Tablet(deviceId, schemas, size);
        tablet.initBitMaps();
        long timestamp = System.currentTimeMillis();
        for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
            tablet.addTimestamp(i, timestamp);
            tablet.rowSize++;
            tablet.addValue("x", i, 1d);
            tablet.addValue("y", i, 2d);
            tablet.addValue("speed", i, 3d);
            timestamp++;
        }
        try {
            sessionPool.insertTablet(tablet, false);
        } catch (IoTDBConnectionException | StatementExecutionException e) {
            throw new RuntimeException(e);
        }
        tablet.reset();
    }
```
You should make sure `tablet.rowSize` not be zero.

